<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Code of Conduct - D'amour Muslim | Community Guidelines</title>
  <meta name="description" content="D'amour Muslim community code of conduct and guidelines. Learn about respectful behaviour, Islamic etiquette, and platform rules for our Muslim matrimonial service.">
  <meta name="keywords" content="D'amour Muslim code of conduct, matrimony guidelines, Muslim marriage platform rules, Islamic etiquette, community guidelines, user behaviour">
  
  <!-- Open Graph / Social Media -->
  <meta property="og:title" content="Code of Conduct - D'amour Muslim">
  <meta property="og:description" content="Community guidelines and standards of behaviour for D'amour Muslim matrimonial platform. Building a respectful environment for marriage connections.">
  <meta property="og:type" content="website">
  <meta property="og:url" content="https://damourmuslim.com/code-of-conduct">

  <!-- Tailwind CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/output.css">
  <!-- Remix Icons -->
  <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/remixicon@3.5.0/fonts/remixicon.css" rel="stylesheet">

  <!-- Custom CSS -->
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">

  <style>
    .conduct-card {
      border-left: 4px solid #4a7c59;
      transition: transform 0.2s ease, box-shadow 0.2s ease;
    }
    .conduct-card:hover {
      transform: translateX(4px);
    }
    .warning-card {
      border-left: 4px solid #dc2626;
    }
    .do-item {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 28px;
    }
    .do-item::before {
      content: '\2713';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 2px;
      color: #4a7c59;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
    .dont-item {
      position: relative;
      padding-left: 28px;
    }
    .dont-item::before {
      content: '\2717';
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 2px;
      color: #dc2626;
      font-weight: bold;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body class="bg-gray-50 font-['Roboto']">
  <%- include('partials/header') %>

  <main class="pt-24 pb-16 min-h-screen">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <!-- Header Section -->
      <div class="text-center mb-8">
        <div class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-16 h-16 bg-[#4a7c59]/10 rounded-full mb-4">
          <i class="ri-hand-heart-line text-3xl text-[#4a7c59]"></i>
        </div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 font-['Playfair_Display']">Code of Conduct</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">Community Guidelines for D'amour Muslim</p>
        <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4 mt-4 text-sm text-gray-500">
          <span class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <i class="ri-calendar-line"></i>
            Effective Date: June 2, 2025
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Islamic Values Banner -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-[#4a7c59] to-[#2d5a3a] rounded-2xl p-6 text-white mb-8 shadow-lg">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
          <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-white/20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <i class="ri-heart-3-line text-3xl"></i>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mb-1">Built on Islamic Values</h2>
            <p class="text-white/90">
              D'amour Muslim is a platform rooted in Islamic principles of honesty, modesty, and respect. By using our platform, you agree to uphold these values and treat all members with dignity befitting the sacred nature of marriage.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Main Content -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl p-8 material-shadow">
        <!-- Introduction -->
        <div class="mb-8">
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            This Code of Conduct outlines the expected behaviour and community standards for all users of D'amour Muslim. Our platform exists to facilitate meaningful marriage connections within a safe, respectful, and Islamic environment. We expect all members to contribute positively to our community and to use the platform with sincerity and good intentions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 1: Core Principles -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-star-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            1. Core Principles
          </h2>
          
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="conduct-card bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
              <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                <i class="ri-heart-line text-[#4a7c59] text-xl mr-2"></i>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Sincerity (Ikhlas)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Use the platform with genuine intention to find a spouse. Do not waste others' time or engage in any activity that is not marriage-focused.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="conduct-card bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
              <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                <i class="ri-shield-check-line text-[#4a7c59] text-xl mr-2"></i>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Honesty (Sidq)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Provide accurate and truthful information in your profile. Misrepresentation harms others and goes against Islamic teachings.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="conduct-card bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
              <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                <i class="ri-user-heart-line text-[#4a7c59] text-xl mr-2"></i>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Respect (Ihtiram)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Treat all users with respect and dignity, regardless of whether you're interested in them. Every person deserves kind treatment.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="conduct-card bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
              <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                <i class="ri-eye-off-line text-[#4a7c59] text-xl mr-2"></i>
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Modesty (Haya)</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Maintain Islamic standards of modesty in all interactions. Keep conversations appropriate and focused on the purpose of marriage.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 2: Profile Guidelines -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-profile-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            2. Profile Guidelines
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Your profile is your introduction to potential families. It should accurately represent your child (or yourself) and be created with the intention of facilitating a lawful marriage.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
              <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-5">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                  <i class="ri-checkbox-circle-fill text-green-600 mr-2"></i>
                  DO
                </h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-green-800">
                  <li class="do-item">Provide accurate personal information</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Use recent, clear, and modest photos</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Be honest about your circumstances</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Describe yourself/your child honestly</li>
                  <li class="do-item">State genuine preferences respectfully</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Keep your profile up to date</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Write in a respectful, professional tone</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                  <i class="ri-close-circle-fill text-red-600 mr-2"></i>
                  DON'T
                </h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-red-800">
                  <li class="dont-item">Use fake names or identities</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Upload inappropriate or old photos</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Lie about age, education, or status</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Exaggerate or misrepresent facts</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Include offensive or haram content</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Create multiple accounts</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Use the platform for purposes other than marriage</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 3: Sending Interest Requests -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-send-plane-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            3. Sending Interest Requests
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Sending an interest request is the first step in initiating a potential match. This should be done thoughtfully and with genuine interest.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-5 my-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2 flex items-center">
                <i class="ri-information-line mr-2"></i>
                How Requests Work
              </h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-blue-800 space-y-1">
                <li>• You can have up to <strong>5 pending requests</strong> at any time</li>
                <li>• When you send a request, your profile information (except phone number) is shared with the recipient</li>
                <li>• The recipient can choose to accept or reject your request</li>
                <li>• If accepted, both parties can view full profiles and begin chatting</li>
                <li>• You can cancel a pending request before it's responded to</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mt-6 mb-3">Expected Behaviour When Sending Requests:</h4>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
              <li><strong>Be selective:</strong> Review profiles carefully before sending requests. Don't send requests indiscriminately.</li>
              <li><strong>Be patient:</strong> Give recipients time to respond. Don't expect immediate replies.</li>
              <li><strong>Accept decisions gracefully:</strong> If your request is rejected, accept it with grace. Do not attempt to contact the person through other means.</li>
              <li><strong>Manage your requests:</strong> Cancel requests that you no longer wish to pursue rather than letting them sit indefinitely.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 4: Responding to Requests -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-reply-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            4. Responding to Requests
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              When you receive an interest request, you have the option to accept or reject it. Both responses should be made with consideration and respect.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mt-6">
              <div class="conduct-card bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">When Accepting</h4>
                <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                  <li>• Your profile information will be shared back with the sender</li>
                  <li>• A chat conversation will be opened</li>
                  <li>• Engage with genuine interest and good intentions</li>
                  <li>• Be prepared to have meaningful conversations about marriage</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="conduct-card bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">When Declining</h4>
                <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 space-y-2">
                  <li>• It's perfectly acceptable to decline requests</li>
                  <li>• No explanation is required</li>
                  <li>• Decline promptly rather than leaving requests pending</li>
                  <li>• Be respectful—everyone is someone's child</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
              <p class="text-amber-800 text-sm">
                <i class="ri-information-line mr-1"></i>
                <strong>Revoking Access:</strong> After accepting a request, you can revoke access at any time if you feel the connection isn't appropriate. The other party will no longer be able to message you or view your full profile.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 5: Communication Guidelines -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-chat-3-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            5. Communication Guidelines
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Once connected, you can communicate through our secure chat system. All conversations should be conducted with Islamic etiquette and the seriousness befitting a marriage discussion.
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mt-6">
              <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-5">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-green-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                  <i class="ri-checkbox-circle-fill text-green-600 mr-2"></i>
                  Appropriate Communication
                </h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-green-800">
                  <li class="do-item">Discuss marriage-related topics</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Ask about family, values, and deen</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Share relevant information about yourself</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Be prompt and courteous in responses</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Involve wali/family when appropriate</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Keep conversations halal and purposeful</li>
                  <li class="do-item">Be clear about your intentions</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5">
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-3 flex items-center">
                  <i class="ri-close-circle-fill text-red-600 mr-2"></i>
                  Prohibited Communication
                </h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-red-800">
                  <li class="dont-item">Flirtatious or romantic messages</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Inappropriate or suggestive content</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Requests for inappropriate photos</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Harassment or repeated unwanted contact</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Rude, offensive, or insulting language</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Threats or intimidation</li>
                  <li class="dont-item">Spam or promotional content</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 mt-4">
              <p class="text-blue-800 text-sm">
                <i class="ri-shield-check-line mr-1"></i>
                <strong>Privacy Note:</strong> Chat conversations may be reviewed by administrators for safety and moderation purposes. This helps us maintain a safe environment for all users.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 6: Prohibited Behaviour -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-prohibited-line text-red-600 mr-2"></i>
            6. Prohibited Behaviour
          </h2>
          
          <div class="warning-card bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-6">
            <p class="text-red-800 mb-4">
              The following behaviours are strictly prohibited and will result in immediate account suspension or permanent ban:
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">Fraud & Deception</h4>
                <ul class="text-sm text-red-800 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Creating fake profiles or impersonation</li>
                  <li>• Using the platform for scams or fraud</li>
                  <li>• Providing deliberately false information</li>
                  <li>• Using stolen photos or identities</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">Harassment & Abuse</h4>
                <ul class="text-sm text-red-800 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Harassing, stalking, or intimidating users</li>
                  <li>• Sending abusive or threatening messages</li>
                  <li>• Continuing contact after being blocked/rejected</li>
                  <li>• Discriminatory or hateful behaviour</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">Inappropriate Content</h4>
                <ul class="text-sm text-red-800 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Sharing explicit or inappropriate content</li>
                  <li>• Uploading immodest or revealing photos</li>
                  <li>• Using vulgar or offensive language</li>
                  <li>• Promoting haram activities</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
              
              <div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 mb-2">Misuse of Platform</h4>
                <ul class="text-sm text-red-800 space-y-1">
                  <li>• Using the platform for dating (not marriage)</li>
                  <li>• Soliciting money from other users</li>
                  <li>• Creating multiple accounts</li>
                  <li>• Commercial use or advertising</li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 7: Privacy & Confidentiality -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-lock-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            7. Privacy & Confidentiality
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Protecting the privacy of all users is essential. You must respect others' personal information and maintain confidentiality.
            </p>
            
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
              <li><strong>Keep information confidential:</strong> Do not share other users' profile information, photos, or conversations with third parties without their explicit consent.</li>
              <li><strong>No screenshots:</strong> Do not take or share screenshots of conversations or profiles for purposes other than sharing with your family members involved in the marriage process.</li>
              <li><strong>Contact information:</strong> Do not share phone numbers or contact details obtained through the platform publicly or with others.</li>
              <li><strong>Respect boundaries:</strong> If someone declines to share certain information, respect their decision.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 8: Family Involvement -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-parent-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            8. Family Involvement
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              D'amour Muslim is designed with family involvement in mind. Profiles are typically created by parents or guardians on behalf of their children, ensuring that the marriage process is conducted in a halal manner with proper family oversight.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-[#4a7c59]/10 rounded-lg p-5 mt-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Guidelines for Family Involvement</h4>
              <ul class="text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-2">
                <li>• Profiles should only be created by parents/guardians with the knowledge and consent of their child</li>
                <li>• The wali (guardian) should be involved in communications when appropriate</li>
                <li>• Important decisions should involve the family, not just the individuals</li>
                <li>• Maintain transparency with your family throughout the process</li>
                <li>• Ensure any meetings are conducted in a halal, family-supervised manner</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 9: Reporting Violations -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-alarm-warning-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            9. Reporting Violations
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              If you encounter any behaviour that violates this Code of Conduct, please report it immediately. Your reports help us maintain a safe community.
            </p>
            
            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-5 mt-4">
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">How to Report</h4>
              <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 text-sm">
                <li>Email us at <a href="mailto:contact@damourmuslim.com" class="text-[#4a7c59] hover:underline">contact@damourmuslim.com</a></li>
                <li>Include the username or profile of the person you're reporting</li>
                <li>Describe the violation in detail</li>
                <li>Attach any relevant evidence (screenshots, if appropriate)</li>
              </ol>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">
              All reports are reviewed by our team. We take all reports seriously and will take appropriate action, which may include warning, suspension, or permanent ban.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 10: Consequences -->
        <div class="mb-8 pb-6 border-b border-gray-200">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-error-warning-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            10. Consequences of Violations
          </h2>
          
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Violations of this Code of Conduct will result in appropriate action based on the severity of the offence:
            </p>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 mt-6">
              <div class="bg-yellow-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-yellow-200">
                <div class="text-center mb-3">
                  <i class="ri-alert-line text-yellow-600 text-2xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-yellow-900 text-center mb-2">Warning</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-yellow-800 text-center">For first-time minor violations</p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-orange-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-orange-200">
                <div class="text-center mb-3">
                  <i class="ri-timer-line text-orange-600 text-2xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-orange-900 text-center mb-2">Temporary Suspension</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-orange-800 text-center">For repeated or moderate violations</p>
              </div>
              
              <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
                <div class="text-center mb-3">
                  <i class="ri-forbid-line text-red-600 text-2xl"></i>
                </div>
                <h4 class="font-semibold text-red-900 text-center mb-2">Permanent Ban</h4>
                <p class="text-sm text-red-800 text-center">For severe or repeated violations</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-4">
              Serious violations (fraud, harassment, illegal activity) will result in immediate permanent ban without warning. We may also report illegal activities to relevant authorities.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Section 11: Conclusion -->
        <div class="mb-6">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 font-['Playfair_Display']">
            <i class="ri-heart-3-line text-[#4a7c59] mr-2"></i>
            Our Commitment to You
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700">
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              By maintaining these standards, we aim to create a platform where families can search for suitable marriage matches with peace of mind. Every user plays a role in maintaining this environment.
            </p>
            <p class="leading-relaxed">
              Marriage is half of our deen, and we take the responsibility of facilitating this sacred institution seriously. We ask that you join us in making D'amour Muslim a respectful, safe, and effective platform for Muslim families.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Final Note -->
        <div class="bg-[#4a7c59]/10 rounded-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <i class="ri-book-open-line text-[#4a7c59] text-xl mr-3 mt-0.5"></i>
            <div>
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Agreement to Code of Conduct</h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
                By using D'amour Muslim, you agree to abide by this Code of Conduct. We reserve the right to update these guidelines as needed to ensure the safety and integrity of our community. Users will be notified of any significant changes.
              </p>
